Day 3 began with us learning other Kali Linus commands
  1. cd - it is used to move from one folder to another
  clear - it is used to clear everything on the terminal
  touch - it is used to create an empty file
  echo - it is used to write tedxt line into a file directly from the terminal
  cat -  it is used to read or display the content of a file
  nano - it is used to create file, add a text into it. you use control o or control s to save after typing and control x to exist.
  mkdir - it is used to create a new folder
  cp: means copy, it is used to copy files from one location to another
  mv - means move. it is used to move or rename files
  rm - it is used to remove or delete files


